SIMPLE: circumcision
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Circumcision
<hw>Cir`cum*cision</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>circumcisio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of cutting off
the prepuce or foreskin of males, or the internal labia of
females.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>circumcision</xex> of males is practiced as a
religious rite by the Jews, Muslims, etc. Circumcision of male infants
is also a common practice as a hygienic measure, to reduce incidence of
infection of the penis.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Script.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The Jews, as a
circumcised people.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Rejection of the sins of the
flesh; spiritual purification, and acceptance of the Christian
faith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Circumclusion</ent>⟦br⟧
